To examine the possible recombination events in the S1 genes of the 2014–2016 Thai IBVs, all 120 Thai IBVs were analyzed using RDP4 and SimPlot softwares. Among the 120 Thai IBVs, a total of 2 Thai IBV isolates (TH/IBV/2014/CU-179 and TH/IBV/2016/CU-92) were identified as a recombinant IBV variant. Recombination analysis demonstrated that this recombinant variant originated from TH/IBV/2016/CU-123 (GI-19 lineage virus) as a major parent and TH/IBV/2016/CU-99 (GI-13 lineage virus) as a minor parent (Table 1
; Figure 3
). The positions of the recombination break point in TH/IBV/2014/CU-179 and TH/IBV/2016/CU-92 were located at 891 nt and 918 nt in the S1 gene, respectively (Table 1). The recombination events were further confirmed by SimPlot software, which also showed similar findings with RDP4 software (data not shown).
